Abducted National Youth Leader of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Rt. Hon. Sunday Udeh-Okoye has regained his freedom. DAILY POST had reported that the Police Command in Enugu State on Tuesday confirmed his abduction. The victim is a former member of Enugu State House of Assembly. The former lawmaker was kidnapped on Monday evening at about 7 p.m. while returning from his farm in Agbogugu community in Awgu Local Government Area of the state. The Command’s Public Relations Officer, SP Ebere Amaraizu, who confirmed the abduction to newsmen in Enugu, said that the masked men are being trailed and a positive result was being expected from the operation. He said, “We are on the trail of his abductors who allegedly kidnapped him from his farm axis in Agbogugu community.” Amaraizu equally said that those that abducted the lawmakers might have known him as they masked themselves in order to hide their identity. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.